        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:17PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Chester, or 5 miles west of Lowrys, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rock Hill, Mcconnells, Lowrys, and Bullock Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
